{"id":305796287,"lang":"python3","lang_name":"Python3","time":"3 years, 6 months","timestamp":1582396317,"status":10,"status_display":"Accepted","runtime":"72 ms","url":"/submissions/detail/305796287/","is_pending":"Not Pending","title":"Add Two Numbers","memory":"12.7 MB","code":"# Definition for singly-linked list.\n# class ListNode:\n#     def __init__(self, x):\n#         self.val = x\n#         self.next = None\n\nclass Solution:\n    def addTwoNumbers(self, l1: ListNode, l2: ListNode) -> ListNode:\n        carry = 0\n        # sentinel node\n        res = ListNode(0)\n        head = res\n        while l1 or l2:\n            p = l1.val if l1 else 0\n            q = l2.val if l2 else 0\n            summ = (p + q + carry) % 10\n            carry = (p + q + carry) // 10\n            head.next = ListNode(summ)\n            head = head.next\n            l1 = l1.next if l1 else None\n            l2 = l2.next if l2 else None\n        if carry > 0:\n            head.next = ListNode(carry)\n        return res.next","compare_result":"","title_slug":"add-two-numbers","has_notes":false,"flag_type":1}
